🚗 Parking Lot System (Python | OOP)
📌 Overview
This project is a Parking Lot Management System implemented in Java using Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) principles. It is part of my learning journey to understand how real-world systems can be designed using clean, modular, and scalable code.
🎯 Objective
The primary goals of this project are:

To apply core OOP concepts in a practical scenario
To model a real-world parking system
To improve problem-solving and system design skills
To track and showcase my learning progress

⚙️ Features

Create and manage parking slots
Park and unpark vehicles
Support multiple vehicle types (Car, Bike, Truck, etc.)
Track available and occupied slots
Structured and modular class design

🧠 OOP Concepts Used

Classes & Objects
Encapsulation
Inheritance (Vehicle types)
Polymorphism
Abstraction

🛠️ Tech Stack

Language: Python
IDE: VS Code 
